Class MeshLoader

java.lang.Object
  EigenMeat.EigenMaze.MeshLoader
public class MeshLoader
extends java.lang.Object

A factory class for creating standard meshes. Unique meshes are cached.

getMesh

public static Mesh getMesh(java.lang.String name)
Gets a cached mesh by name. Not all meshes are cached by their given name - many have suffixes related to size or texture data.

Parameters:
name - the name of the Mesh to retrieve.
Returns:
The cached Mesh matching the name, or null if no such Mesh is cached.

Create a rectangular prism (box) with specified dimensions and cache it.

Parameters:
name - the name under which to cache this Mesh.

y - the y dimension (height) of the box.
z - the z dimension (depth) of the box.

createBox

public static Mesh createBox(java.lang.String name,
                             float x,
                             float y,
                             float z,
                             java.lang.String texture)
Create a rectangular prism (box) with specified dimensions and texture and cache it. The Mesh will actually be cached under the name String(name+"+"+texture).

Parameters:
name - the base name under which to cache this Mesh.
x - the x dimension (width) of the box.
y - the y dimension (height) of the box.
z - the z dimension (depth) of the box.
texture - the filepath of the texture to be used.
Returns:
The box Mesh with specified dimensions and texture, centered at (0,0,0).

loadMesh

public static Mesh loadMesh(java.lang.String filepath,
                            float scale)
Loads a mesh object from a Wavefront OBJ file, complete with color and UV texture mapping if applicable. This method recognizes only a subset of the Wavefront format corresponding to the features of the engine.

Parameters:
filepath - the filepath to the model file.
scale - the scale at which to generate the resulting Mesh.
Returns:
the Mesh representing the scaled and textured model.

loadOldMesh

Parameters:

Returns:
the Mesh generated from the file.
